widest uppercase text-xs">Request an Appointment</a></div></header><main id="main-content"><section class="bg-charcoal text-white py-20"><div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center"><div><nav class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-teal mb-6"><a href="/">Home</a> / Single Tooth Implant</nav><p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-teal mb-4">Single Tooth Implants</p><h1 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl font-light leading-tight mb-6">Single Tooth Dental Implants</h1><p class="text-white/70 leading-8 text-lg mb-8">A single dental implant can replace one missing tooth without reshaping the neighboring teeth for a traditional bridge.</p><div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4"><a href="/#contact" class="inline-block bg-teal px-8 py-4 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest font-semibold text-center">Request an Appointment</a><a href="tel:+12546994127" class="inline-block border border-teal px-8 py-4 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest font-semibold text-teal text-center">Call 254-699-4127</a></div></div><div><img src="/single-tooth-implant-ai.webp" alt="Single tooth dental implant illustration at Elm Ridge Implant and Family Dentistry in Killeen, TX" class="w-full shadow-2xl" loading="eager" decoding="async"  width="1672" height="941"/></div></div></section><section class="py-16 bg-white"><div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 prose-page space-y-7"><p>When one tooth is missing, patients often compare a removable partial, a traditional bridge, and a single implant. A single implant is designed to replace the tooth root and support an individual crown.</p><h2>How Treatment Is Planned</h2><p>Dr. Jeff Muszynski uses CBCT imaging to evaluate bone width, bone height, root spacing, and nearby anatomy before recommending implant placement. The final crown shape and bite are part of the plan from the beginning.</p><h2>Timing and Cost Factors</h2><p>Some single implant cases are straightforward. Others require extraction, grafting, healing time, a temporary tooth option, or additional esthetic planning for a front tooth.</p><h2>Why Patients Choose Elm Ridge</h2><p>Implant placement and restoration are coordinated in one privately owned office, so patients can ask about surgery, healing, the crown, comfort options, and financing without being passed between separate offices.</p></div></section><section class="py-16 bg-charcoal text-white text-center"><div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6"><h2 class="font-display text-4xl mb-4">Ready for a clearer plan?</h2><p class="text-white/65 mb-8">Schedule a visit with Elm Ridge Implant and Family Dentistry in Killeen.</p><a href="/#contact" class="inline-block bg-teal px-8 py-4 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest font-semibold">Request an Appointment</a></div></section><section class="py-12 bg-stone"><div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 border border-teal-light bg-white p-7"><h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-charcoal mb-3">After Implant Treatment</h2><p class="text-charcoal/65 leading-7 mb-5">Review healing instructions for dental implant surgery and bone grafting before or after your appointment.</p><div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3"><a href="/post-operative-instructions#implants" class="inline-block bg-teal px-6 py-3 text-center font-body text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-white">Dental Implant Instructions</a><a href="/post-operative-instructions#bone-graft" class="inline-block border border-teal px-6 py-3 text-center font-body text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-teal-dark">Bone Graft Instructions</a></div></div></section><section class="py-12 bg-white"><div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 border border-teal-light bg-stone p-7"><h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-charcoal mb-3">Dental Implant Insurance</h2><p class="text-charcoal/65 leading-7 mb-5">Implant coverage varies widely. Learn how benefits, exclusions, annual maximums, and financing may apply.</p><a href="/insurance/implants" class="inline-block bg-teal px-6 py-3 text-center font-body text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-white">Learn About Implant Insurance</a></div></section><section id="implant-faq-enhancement" class="py-16 bg-stone"><div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6"><h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-charcoal mb-8">Dental Implant FAQ</h2><div class="space-y-4"><details class="bg-white border border-teal-light p-6"><summary class="font-semibold text-charcoal">How long does a single tooth implant take to heal?</summary><p class="mt-3 text-charcoal/65 leading-7">A single tooth implant commonly heals for about 3 to 4 months before the final crown is made.</p></details><details class="bg-white border border-teal-light p-6"><summary class="font-semibold text-charcoal">Does a single implant protect nearby teeth?</summary><p class="mt-3 text-charcoal/65 leading-7">A single implant can replace one missing tooth without reshaping the neighboring teeth for a traditional bridge.</p></details></div></div></section></main><footer class="bg-charcoal pt-16 pb-8"><div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6"><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-12 mb-12"><div><div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-24 h-24 bg-teal overflow-hidden mb-5"><img src="/square logo.webp" alt="Elm Ridge Implant and Family Dentistry logo in Killeen, TX" class="w-20 h-20 object-contain" loading="lazy" decoding="async"  width="515" height="515"/></div><h3 class="font-display text-xl font-light text-white mb-3" style="letter-spacing:0.04em;">Elm Ridge Implant<br />and Family Dentistry</h3><p class="font-body text-sm text-white/45 leading-relaxed">A practice built on lasting relationships and exceptional care.</p></div><div><p class="font-body text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-teal mb-5">Navigation</p><ul class="space-y-3"><li><a href="/#services" class="font-body text-sm text-white/55 hover:text-white">Services</a></li><li><a href="/dental-implants-killeen-tx" class="font-body text-sm text-white/55 hover:text-white">I